.TH "am33xx_prm_is_hardreset_asserted" 9 "am33xx_prm_is_hardreset_asserted" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
am33xx_prm_is_hardreset_asserted \- read the HW reset line state of submodules contained in the hwmod module
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" am33xx_prm_is_hardreset_asserted
.BI "(u8 shift "  ","
.BI "u8 part "  ","
.BI "s16 inst "  ","
.BI "u16 rstctrl_offs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "shift" 12
register bit shift corresponding to the reset line to check
.IP "part" 12
PRM partition, ignored for AM33xx
.IP "inst" 12
CM instance register offset (*_INST macro)
.IP "rstctrl_offs" 12
RM_RSTCTRL register address offset for this module
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 1 if the (sub)module hardreset line is currently asserted,
0 if the (sub)module hardreset line is not currently asserted, or
-EINVAL upon parameter error.
